Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.780 --> 00:00:04.630
&gt;&gt; From the Library of
Congress in Washington, D.C.

00:00:18.370 --> 00:00:19.700
&gt;&gt; Paulette Hasier:
Good morning.

00:00:19.700 --> 00:00:22.020
My name is Dr. Paulette
Hasier, and I'm the chief

00:00:22.020 --> 00:00:23.700
of the geography and
math division here

00:00:23.700 --> 00:00:25.000
at the Library of Congress.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.140
I would like to welcome you
and thank you all for coming

00:00:28.140 --> 00:00:32.730
to the Library of
Congress GIS Day Event.

00:00:32.730 --> 00:00:35.490
We are really excited to
share the depth and breadth

00:00:35.490 --> 00:00:39.210
of geospatial tools and data
and how they're being used

00:00:39.210 --> 00:00:42.040
to support Congress and
how they're also being used

00:00:42.040 --> 00:00:43.340
to support the library here.

00:00:43.340 --> 00:00:46.590
In this morning's
session you will hear

00:00:46.590 --> 00:00:49.810
from our esteemed Congressional
members and representatives

00:00:49.810 --> 00:00:51.600
from the Congressional
Research Service

00:00:51.600 --> 00:00:55.370
on how GIS data can
inform policy.

00:00:55.370 --> 00:00:59.310
In our afternoon session, we
will treat you to a showcase

00:00:59.310 --> 00:01:03.790
of GIS story maps and how this
tool has revolutionized the way

00:01:03.790 --> 00:01:08.210
we support digital humanities
and digital visualization.

00:01:08.210 --> 00:01:10.690
I would, however, be remiss
if I did not thank those

00:01:10.690 --> 00:01:12.580
who made this day possible.

00:01:12.580 --> 00:01:16.210
I would like to acknowledge
Congressman Takano

00:01:16.210 --> 00:01:18.580
for taking the time out
of his busy schedule

00:01:18.580 --> 00:01:20.780
to give us first-hand
insights on how GIS

00:01:20.780 --> 00:01:24.590
and geospatial data is
being used in Congress.

00:01:24.590 --> 00:01:29.020
The GIS Program would not
be possible if it was not

00:01:29.020 --> 00:01:31.990
for the support the
of our OCIO staff,

00:01:31.990 --> 00:01:35.280
our GI [inaudible]
staff, and our CRS staff.

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:39.540
Special tanks are extended to
Dr. Mary Mazanec and [inaudible]

00:01:39.540 --> 00:01:41.390
of the Congressional
Research Service

00:01:41.390 --> 00:01:45.170
for helping plan this day and
for speaking at the event.

00:01:45.170 --> 00:01:47.560
A special thanks to Steve
Kelly and Kathleen Ott

00:01:47.560 --> 00:01:50.140
at the Library Congressional
Relations Office as well

00:01:50.140 --> 00:01:51.610
for their help and guidance.

00:01:51.610 --> 00:01:58.760
Also a deep appreciation
for the [inaudible] staff,

00:01:58.760 --> 00:02:01.930
especially Laurie [inaudible],
who was helpful in scheduling

00:02:01.930 --> 00:02:04.700
and creating this event for us.

00:02:04.700 --> 00:02:08.760
And lastly, I would like
to thank the participants

00:02:08.760 --> 00:02:11.240
